#notakembara Ibu.. Aku kembara lagi Hidup di kota besar aku banyak di lenakan oleh keadaan.. Dimanjakan dengan semua fasilitas yang ada.. .Entah.. Ibu.. Kini aku kembara.. Kembara untuk melihat keagungan ciptaan tuhan semesta alam.. Ibu.. Cerita ini aku tulis tika di Desa Sembalun.. Nusa Tenggara.. Sebuah desa dimana keindahan alam memancarkan indera.. Dari desa ini aku bisa menyaksikan megahnya puncak Rinjani hijaunya padang savannah sembalun.. Ibu.. Aku kembara lagi.. Penjalanan aku kini bukan mudah.. Setiap titis keringat yang menitis.. Meningatkan aku tentang kebesaran yang Maha Esa.. Namun.. Berkat doamu ibu.. Puncak Rinjani bisa aku tawani.. . . Philippines own sand dunes found only in the the province of Ilocos.  Not the typical desert but the sand dunes in Paoay is definitely a tourist destination not only for the foreigners but for the locals as well. Activities include sand boarding and the offroad ride that will surely leave your body in pain a day after. A unique northern experience indeed.  ____________ Dec.2014. Photo taken using #GoPro #Hero3  Edited using #Snapseed and #iWatermark   #Paoay #IlocosNorte #Philippines #sand #dunes #north      All Rights Reserved. 2015.

. Another church. Immaculate Conception Church in Batac Ilocos Norte.  There are many churches in the province of Ilocos. Most of them are heritage sites that have stood through time. The stoned walls have stories to tell the tale of the Philippines historic north which was of course about the Spanish influence during their rule of the country.  ____________ Dec.2014. Photo taken using #GoPro #Hero3  Edited using #Snapseed and #iWatermark   #Batac #IlocosNorte #Philippines #church #north      All Rights Reserved. 2015.

. First stop Bantay Church and Bell Tower Ilocos Sur.  This was my first time to climb all the way to the top of a bell tower. The structure showed its age though very well maintained. The view from the top was astounding. The sun rose over the mountain range that morning and casted a shadow on the landscape beneath  it. The first of many more amazing sceneries to see.  ____________ Dec.2014. The Sacred Bridge ( shinky?) crossing the Daiya River belongs to the Futarasan Shrine. This beautiful vermilion lacquered structure is known as one of the three most beautiful bridges in Japan and is a perfect gateway for Nikko. The bridge was registered as a World Heritage in December 1999. Shinkyo measures 28 meters long 7.4 meters wide and stands 10.6 meters above the Daiya River. #wikipedia

Nikk ( Nikkshi? literally    sunlight    or    sunshine   ) is a city in the mountains of Tochigi Prefecture Japan. Approximately 140 km north of Tokyo and 35 km west of Utsunomiya the capital of Tochigi Prefecture it is a popular destination for Japanese and international tourists. #wikipedia

The Great Buddha of Kamakura is a monumental outdoor bronze statue of Amitbha Buddha located at the Ktokuin Temple in Kamakura Kanagawa Prefecture Japan. The bronze statue probably dates from 1252 in the Kamakura period according to temple records. #wikipedia
KAMAKURA  There is beauty in all we know and beauty in all we dont know. Our journey is to love it all.  Thomas Warfield

The temple is built on two levels and also includes an underground cave. The grounds of the temple are home to hundreds of small Jiz statues placed by parents mourning offspring lost to miscarriage stillbirth or abortion. #wikipedia

Sagami Bay ( Sagamiwan? also known as the Sagami Gulf or Sagami Sea) lies south of Kanagawa Prefecture in Honshu central Japan contained within the scope of the Miura Peninsula in Kanagawa to the east the Izu Peninsula in Shizuoka Prefecture to the west and the Shnan coastline to the north while the island of Izu shima marks the southern extent of the bay. It lies approximately 40 kilometres (25 mi) southwest of the capital Tokyo. Cities on the bay include Odawara Chigasaki Fujisawa Hiratsuka Ito and Kamakura. #wikipedia
SHORO BELFRY  The temple originally belonged to the Tendai sect of Buddhism but eventually became an independent temple of the Jdo sh sect. #wikipedia

Hasedera ( Kaikzan Jishin Hasedera?) commonly called the Hasekannon (?) is one of the great Buddhist temples in the city of Kamakura in Kanagawa Prefecture Japan famous for housing a massive wooden statue of Kannon. The temple is the fourth of the 33 stations of the Band Sanjsankasho pilgrimage circuit dedicated to the goddess Benzaiten. #wikipedia

I miss India!  #throwback #Kochi #Kerala #SouthIndia #INDIA     #travelinstyle  Nasib setiap hamba Allah kat muka Bumi tak sama. Berlainan rezeki. Ada yang dapat lebih rezeki ada yang dapat kurang tp yang dapat kurang tu mesti Tuhan bagi kelebihan dari aspect lain mungkin. Sebab Allah itu maha Adil. Sama jugak dgn jodoh. Ada yg dapat jodoh cepat ada yang lambat.  Dalam kehidupan seharian aku dan dikelilingi oleh insan2 yang selalu ckp mcm ni dkt aku xpa la tak kahwin lg bole p jalan2 merata. Sorang2 senang xdak komitmen. Errrr..aku sendiri pelik. Mereka2 ni tak pernah single ka. Lahir2 terus kahwin ka? Or tiba2 Bumi ni baru wujud nak dijelajah? Aku sendiri yg single ni komitmen byk jugak weii..Mcm hutang korang kena bayar macam tu jugak aku kena bayar. Dan kenapa nak dijadikan status perkahwinan itu sebagai halangan. Dan paling aku tak suka anak dijadikan alasan. Alasannya susah nak jaga. Aku pernah jumpa 1 couple ni masa dekat Krabi. Best ja dorang p jalan2 n then tinggai anak kat mak bapak tlg jaga.  #typicalmalaysian Aku tgk mat2 salleh OK ja bawa 1 family travel siap posing 1 dunia lg. Personally bagi aku aku tak nak status perkahwinan tu sebagai halangan utk kita nak travel. Mungkin kadar per tahun utk kita keluar dari negara ni mungkin berkurang sedikit compare ketika masih single. Its better than nothing kan. Kalo dah sama2 minat travel lg best kan. Dia jugak soulmate kita dia jugak travel partner kita.  Hopefully Alyah menang mlm ni. Bole bayar buat repair Audi Dato Ramli tu. Haha #AJL29

#throwback #AngkorWat #Cambodia    Aku suka Cambodia esp Siem Reap.  Aku pon tak taw kenapa dan mengapa aku suka travel negara2 usang mcm ni??  Aku tak taw pasaipa hari ini byk TERjumpa org2 masa lalu aku. Wow depa dh move. Aku ja yg dok mcm ni dr dulu smp sekarang. Yup! Aku jealous. Mana tak nya. Dulu dia yg dok tny aku mcm mn nk belit2 shawl bagai. Last2 dia yg fashionable lg dr aku. Its ok. At least berubah ke arah kebaikan kn.  Sometime aku rasa mcm nk hidup normal mcm org2 sekeliling aku. #TypicalMalaysian  Sometime aku rasa mcm malas nak backpack. Mcm nk jd tourist ja p melancong. Senang hidup kn.  Sometime aku rasa nk stop travel ja. So annual leave yg ada tu bole simpan utk cuti raya smp seminggu. N bole guna cuti tu relax2 kt umah tgk TV. Mcm org2 lain. Org2 sekeliling aku.  Trip yg plg penat aku buat trip ThailandLaos. Trip yg terkejar2 dgn masa. Mana tak nya tak penat esok tu aku dah kena keje. Aku bukan jenis EL @ MC sesuka hati. Dlm thn ni baru sekali ja aku MC. Kagum tak? Haha #pekerjacemerlanglasangat Even ms aku p langkawi hari tu pon ak smp png airport dlm 10.30pg ( 1/2 jam ja pon LANGKAWIPNG lama tak?) Hari tu jugak aku msk ofis pkl 2 ptg blk 8.30mlm. Igt even #cuticutiMalaysia tu tak penat ke?  Bkn aku tak boleh amik cuti pjg2 bole! Tp setahun 1 trip jela pastu dok diam2. Mcm pelancong setahun sekali p bercuti. Mmg tak la. Org luar depa nmpk indah je. Mcm minggu ni aku keje 2 minggu sabtu berturut2..6 hari direct. Ahad ja dpt relax2 OK. Sbb apa? Sbb aku nk guna off day tu utk aku p kenduri kendara kwn2 yg semua tiba2 bole kawin serentak. Sorry! AL aku simpan utk next trip. Cuba bayangkan mcm mn aku kena bajet cuti setiap kali oversea trip aku akn cuti almost 2 weeks. Company bg kt aku AL 16 hari je setahun. Hebat kn? Sumpah penat.  In future maybe aku akan unpaid je selagi status UNPAID tu tak menjejaskan apa2.  Kepada manusia yg TERambil OPPO aku tolong delete semua gambar aku n tolong respect internal docs daily work aku. Hopefully anda tahu apa itu PDPA. Semoga selamat dunia akhirat.

. 1.7 million dead. They call it the killing fields. One of the many monuments where mass killings were made during the communist Khmer Rouge regime this structure in Choeung Ek contains stacked skulls of those who were slain. It is believed that 1.7 to 2.5 million people died in 1975 out of an 8 million population.  ____________ Jul.2013. . Shopping?  A must see stop when in Cambodias capital the Central Market is a place for extensive amount of goods that are sold for very cheap prices.  The Psah Thom as locals call it is a large market in Phnom Penh that was built in 1937. Yellowdomed it has four hallways that branch out to spaces that house hundreds of stalls selling products from clothes and books to antique coins and religious figurines.  ____________ Jul.2013. . Phnom Penhs oldest pagoda the Wat Ounalom sits along Sisowath Quay. They say it is also the most important pagoda as it served as a repository for an ounalom  a hair from the Buddhas eyebrow.  This temple dates all the way back to the reign of Ponhea Yat in the fifteenth century and holds in its crypt urns of notable Cambodians.  ____________ Jul.2013. . Climbing up for that cold breeze.  Baguio is a city in the province of Benguet located in the northern part of Luzon. . A Douglas A1 Skyraider sitting on the museums yard along with other heavy machineries used during Vietnam War.  The War Remnants Museum in Ho Chi Minh City contains collections from military equipment firearms & explosives to photographs of war and even preserved human fetuses. Along with the photos are texts describing the effects of Americas chemical weapons including the famed Agent Orange.  And though the gallery could easily be onesided and antiAmerican the War Remnants Museum is still a place to be visited in HCMC  but may not be for the fainthearted.  ____________ Jul.2013. Inside the Espousal of Joseph and Mary Chapel in Club Balai Isabel. This chapel is not allowed to hold actual wedding rites. Couples usually have the wedding ceremony in a nearby church the San Guillermo Church and have the reception in one of Club Balais function areas. Couples whod like to walk this aisle will have to get married outside first (marriage certificate is a requirement) and have their wedding here for the show. Chapel rate is 30 thousand pesos inclusive of aircon use and simple floral arrangements. #itsmorefuninthephilippines #wowphilippines #pilipinas #philippines #tlasia #travelph #travelnow #travel2013 #turismo #lakbayph #lakbaypinas #thetraveltagger #bangskidoo #byaherangbang #batangas #chapel #wedding #weddingsph
